        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooled, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>blackened pepper </strong>and discard the top[s]</p><p>Peel off the skin (clean hands is the best way!), then roughly chop the <strong>peeled pepper</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped peeled pepper </strong>and <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>to the <strong>food processor </strong>with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and blitz until a smooth thick paste has formed – this is your <strong>muhammara dip</strong></p>",
